Current diesel has this conversion
```rust
    fn for_input((tpe, data): (MysqlType, Option<Vec<u8>>)) -> Self {
        let (tpe, flags) = tpe.into();
        let is_null = i8::from(data.is_none());
        let mut bytes = data.unwrap_or_default();
        let ptr = NonNull::new(bytes.as_mut_ptr());
        let len = bytes.len() as libc::c_ulong;
        let capacity = bytes.capacity();
        mem::forget(bytes);
        Self {
            tpe,
            bytes: ptr,
            length: len,
            capacity,
            flags,
            is_null,
            is_truncated: None,
        }
    }
```
Notice that `is_null` has type `mysqlclient_sys::my_bool = std::os::raw::c_char` but it receives an `i8`. On certain platforms, `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu` in this case, `c_char` is `u8` thus compile failes.

This PR fix this.

This proc macro implements `Connection` and related traits for an enum of connections for different database backends. This allows to easily support multiple database systems at the same time. I've chosen to implement this feature as a derive, instead of providing just one `AnyConnection` enum with all diesel connection types, to allow third party connection implementations to be used there as well.

The following use:
```rust
#[derive(diesel::MultiConnection)]
pub enum MultiConnection {
    Postgres(PgConnection),
    Mysql(diesel::MysqlConnection),
    Sqlite(diesel::SqliteConnection),
}
```

generates [this implementation](https://gist.github.com/weiznich/19406dde61f5225cd2dc2927a6d33338). It then can be used like this:

```rust
fn main() {
    use diesel::prelude::*;

    diesel::table! {
        users(id) {
            id -> Integer,
            name -> Text,
        }
    }

    // all connection types share the same type
    let mut pg_connection: MultiConnection =
        MultiConnection::establish("postgres://localhost/diesel_test").unwrap();
    let mut sqlite_connection: MultiConnection = MultiConnection::establish(":memory:").unwrap();
    let mut mysql_connection: MultiConnection =
        MultiConnection::establish("mysql://weiznich:diesel@localhost/diesel_tests").unwrap();

    assert!(matches!(&pg_connection, MultiConnection::Postgres(_)));
    assert!(matches!(&sqlite_connection, MultiConnection::Sqlite(_)));
    assert!(matches!(&mysql_connection, MultiConnection::Mysql(_)));

    pg_connection.begin_test_transaction().unwrap();
    sqlite_connection.begin_test_transaction().unwrap();
    mysql_connection.begin_test_transaction().unwrap();

    diesel::sql_query(
        "CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT NOT NULL)",
    )
    .execute(&mut pg_connection)
    .unwrap();

    diesel::sql_query("CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, name TEXT NOT NULL)")
        .execute(&mut sqlite_connection)
        .unwrap();

    diesel::sql_query(
        "CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE users (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT, name TEXT NOT NULL)",
    )
    .execute(&mut mysql_connection)
    .unwrap();

    let insert_statement = diesel::insert_into(users::table).values(users::name.eq("John"));

    insert_statement.execute(&mut pg_connection).unwrap();
    insert_statement.execute(&mut mysql_connection).unwrap();
    insert_statement.execute(&mut sqlite_connection).unwrap();

    // we can execute queries again all of them
    let select_statement = users::table.order_by(users::id).limit(20);
    let res = select_statement
        .load::<(i32, String)>(&mut pg_connection)
        .unwrap();
    dbg!(res);

    let res = select_statement
        .load::<(i32, String)>(&mut mysql_connection)
        .unwrap();
    dbg!(res);

    let res = select_statement
        .load::<(i32, String)>(&mut sqlite_connection)
        .unwrap();
    dbg!(res);

    // execute backend specific queries on the underlying connection
    if let MultiConnection::Postgres(ref mut pg_conn) = pg_connection {
        let res = users::table.load::<(i32, String)>(pg_conn).unwrap();
        dbg!(res);
    }
}
```

After landing this I suggest we use this to reimplement `diesel_cli`, which should remove quite a bit of generic code there. In addition that would allow us to test this feature internally.
